# Normalize line endings in the repo so a Windows checkout can't ship CRLF where it breaks.
* text=auto

# Shell scripts MUST be LF. A CRLF entrypoint.sh makes bash fail on the first directive inside a
# Linux container — e.g. `set -euo pipefail\r` → "set: pipefail: invalid option name" — which
# crash-loops the workspace sandbox image (CrashLoopBackOff) so the agent's tools silently never start.
*.sh text eol=lf

# The workspace-executor container entrypoint and its scripts are Linux-only; pin them to LF.
docker/** text eol=lf
